{{rfd|The word does not exist commonly, it’s just a joke for selling an egg opener. Rainer Zenz (German Wikipedia)}}
==German==

===Etymology===

From ''[[Eierschale]]'' ("egg shell"), ''[[Sollbruchstelle]]'' ("predetermined breaking point"), ''[[Verursacher]]'' ("causer").

===Noun===
'''Eierschalensollbruchstellenverursacher''' {{m}}

# ''A device used to create breaking points in egg shells in order to allow one to easily remove the top part of an egg using a knife without causing the shell to splinter.'' (only used for the humorous effect of the overly formal construction of the word, resembling ''[[Amtsdeutsch]]'')

